{
  "texts": [
    "As a first approximation, the Act uses the amount of compute used for training and sets the initial threshold at 10 25 FLOPs.",
    "Systems above this threshold are presumed to represent systemic risk.",
    "The European legislator furthermore explains in Recital 60n of the AI Act that this threshold of 10 25 FLOPs should be adjusted over time as well as be supplemented with benchmarks and indicators for system capabilities, i.e., means of specification other than compute power.",
    "The Commission is granted an explicit mandate to amend the threshold for compute and adopt such benchmarks and indicators as specifications that, when met, trigger the presumption of systemic risk.",
    "Therefore, from a regulatory perspective, capabilities' specifications play a central role in assessing general-purpose AI systems and categorizing those systems according to their possible risks."
  ]
}